    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The problem is that people don't trust the \"math\" when they feel like it's coming from a black box. The council thinks a committee of local residents—people who actually live in these neighborhoods and understand the racial dynamics—will be way more \"fair\" than your code. They're basically saying that human intuition and lived experience are better at fixing systemic issues than your optimization. Do you think a group of people with those specific community ties can really manage the budget as effectively as you do?",
